    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>If RepairQ is unable to communicate with your PAX device, you may need to update the IP address in your Payment Device settings.</p><h3 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:FindtheIPAddressAssignedtoYourBluefinPAXA80/A920-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934229721/Integrated+Payments+Troubleshooting+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934229721\" data-linked-resource-version=\"19\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payments: Troubleshooting Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786757/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Ping+Your+Device+to+See+if+it+is+Reachable\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786757\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Devices: Ping Your Device to See if it is Reachable</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934197020/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Update+Your+IP+Address+in+RepairQ\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934197020\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Update Your IP Address in RepairQ</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1935572993/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+the+LAN+Type+on+a+Bluefin+PAX+A80+A920\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1935572993\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change the LAN Type on a Bluefin PAX A80/A920</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157/Integrated+Payment+Processing+-+Start+Here\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295157\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Processing - Start Here!</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:FindtheIPAddressAssignedtoYourBluefinPAXA80/A920-RetrievingtheIPAddressassignedtoYourPAXA80(Wi-Fi)\">Retrieving the IP Address assigned to Your PAX A80 (Wi-Fi)</h2><p /><p>1. On your PAX A80, exit the Bluefin Application by pressing the <strong>red Cancel Key</strong>. When prompted to exit, tap <strong>OK </strong>(or press the <strong>green Enter key</strong>).</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the home screen, tap the <strong>Settings icon</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Password screen, enter your password and then tap the <strong>Checkmark </strong>Icon. Then tap <strong>OK</strong>.</p><p>Alternatively, you can enter your password and press the <strong>green Enter key twice</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: The default password for a Bluefin PAX A80 is &quot;9876&quot; or &quot;pax9876@@&quot;. If you need to reset your password, you will need to contact <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.bluefin.com/support/merchant/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluefin Support</a>.</p><p /><p>4. On the Settings page, locate the Wireless &amp; networks section. Under this section, tap\u00a0<strong>Wi-Fi</strong>. You should see your network name under the Wi-Fi header, indicating it is connected.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%204.5.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. (A80) On the list of networks, tap the <strong>Gear Icon</strong> on the top-right of the screen.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: For the A920, tap the active, wireless connection. The IP address and additional details will appear on a pop-up screen.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>6. On the Configure Wi-Fi screen, scroll down to the IP Address section at the bottom of the page. Your address will be at the very bottom of the list.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934196946/A80%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>7. Tap the <strong>Home Button</strong> to return to the home screen and reopen the Bluefin application.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
